# Naming Conventions

## Files & Folders
- **Folders**: `kebab-case` (e.g. `workflow-store`, `use-run-job`)
- **React components**: `PascalCase.tsx` (e.g. `TextInputNode.tsx`, `WorkflowEditor.tsx`, `NodePicker.tsx`)
- **Non-component TypeScript**: `kebab-case.ts` (e.g. `workflow-store.ts`, `use-run-job.ts`, `executor.ts`)
- **API routes**: always `route.ts` inside the appropriate folder
- **Types files**: `kebab-case.ts` in `src/types/` (e.g. `workflow.ts`)

## Exports
- **React components**: named export using `PascalCase` function declaration (e.g. `export function TextInputNode()`)
- **Hooks**: named export prefixed with `use` (e.g. `export function useRunJob()`)
- **Zustand stores**: named export prefixed with `use` (e.g. `export const useWorkflowStore = create(...)`)
- **Utility functions**: named export using `camelCase` (e.g. `export function nanoid()`)
- **Constants**: `SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE` (e.g. `MODEL_REGISTRY`, `POLL_INTERVAL_MS`, `ADMIN_EMAILS`)
- **Types/interfaces**: `PascalCase` (e.g. `WorkflowGraph`, `NodePort`, `ExecutionContext`)

## Component Files
- One primary component per file
- File name matches the exported component name
- Internal sub-components (e.g. `NodeStatusBadge` in `GenerativeNode.tsx`) stay in the same file — don't extract unless reused

## Import Style
- Always use path alias `@/...` — never relative `../../` imports
- Relative imports (`./`) only for sibling files in the same directory
- Group imports: external packages → `@/` aliases → relative `./` — separated by blank lines
